title: For Sale:  Cerakote Application
postcontent: Alright guys heres one for you. After deciding I wanted to cerakote some of my firearms it didnt take much research to find out there wasn't much of an option in the area for application and any of the options online are crazy high priced. Since I already had a setup for powder coating I figured I would set out to apply cerakote myself. After a couple grand invested and far too much time later here we are. After doing many of mine and many for friends and family Ive started doing it on the side as I can apply for a much lower price than the other guys. Ive posted some of my recent work, the 1911 and ak are in the very popular custom blend of burnt bronze and graphite black while the smith is coated in robins egg blue. Cerakote is by far the worlds leading gun coating option and offers many benefits past corrosion resistence and appearance. It can be applied to polymer, wood, and metal and really anything that I can get my hands on to blast and bake. I fully blast, soak and bake according to factory specifications. I use #120 AO media, acetone baths, and my ovens are 24"x28"x70". Im running a Dessicant air dryer system to ensure satisfactory application. Im located in Abingdon so you'll have to arrange to bring your firearm to me or Ill do local pickup as Im in JC area twice a week. Email me on here for pricing and further questions as Im sure you'll have plenty.Sig , 1911 , ak , ar , pistols , rifles , glock , ruger , smith

title: For Sale:  Cerakote Application
postcontent: Alright guys heres one for you. After deciding I wanted to cerakote some of my firearms it didnt take much research to find out there wasn't much of an option in the area for application and any of the options online are crazy high priced. Since I already had a setup for powder coating I figured I would set out to apply cerakote myself. After a couple grand invested and far too much time later here we are. After doing many of mine and many for friends and family Ive started doing it on the side as I can apply for a much lower price than the other guys. Ive posted some of my recent work, the 1911 and ak are in the very popular custom blend of burnt bronze and graphite black while the smith is coated in robins egg blue. Cerakote is by far the worlds leading gun coating option and offers many benefits past corrosion resistence and appearance. It can be applied to polymer, wood, and metal and really anything that I can get my hands on to blast and bake. I fully blast, soak and bake according to factory specifications. I use #120 AO media, acetone baths, and my ovens are 24"x28"x70". Im running a Dessicant air dryer system to ensure satisfactory application. Im located in Abingdon so you'll have to arrange to bring your firearm to me or Ill do local pickup as Im down towards JC twice a week.
